Check the reflexive property
Check the symmetric property
The smallest one containes those relations, we do not need to check the transitive property

Example:
Find the smallest equivalence relation on the set {a, b, c, d, e} containing the relation {(a, b), (a, c), (d, e)}
1. Reflexive: (a,a), (b,b), (c,c), (d,d), (e,e)
2. Symmetric: (a,b), (b,a); (a,c), (c,a); (d,e), (e,d)
So the smallest equivalence relation is {(a,a), (b,b), (c,c), (d,d), (e,e), (a,b), (b,a), (a,c), (c,a), (d,e), (e,d)}
